            <title>[HBASE-6186] Assure thread safety</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6186</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Check data structures for necessary thread safety.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One known issue is as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In TableAuthManager, we need to deal with concurrent grants and revokes now that ADMIN permission can be delegated to perhaps multiple users.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Consider using a ReadWriteLock to protect for update. The current data structure is an array multimap. It is also possible to obtain a synchronized multimap from Guava with Multimaps#synchronizedListMultimap but by far the most common access is read access, and concurrent read access is fine.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
